-- World's biggest banks to meet in London: report
-- 
-- Sat Mar 7, 2009 3:08pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/03/07/us-banks-meeting-idUSTRE52627820090307

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Chief executives of leading banks from Japan, Europe and the United States will meet in London to discuss regulation of the financial sector, AFP news agency reported, citing the Nikkei economic daily. 

 According to the report, which did not name sources, the British government will host the meeting on March 24, after the Group of 20 (G-20) finance ministers meeting in London this coming weekend. The report said invitations had been sent to leading institutions including JPMorgan and HSBC. It said Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group president Nobuo Kuroyanagi would attend. Leaders of the G-20 nations are due to meet in London on April 2. (New York Desk, +1 646 223 6200)